From Steve Brinich Subject Re Once tapped your code is no good any Maybe so but it's quite There are millions of Macintosh users who have no idea what's in Apple's patented Many have modems How do you know all your business secrets aren't being stolen Answer Because you trust Apple Because if any such attempt however sophicsticated came out it would destroy Apple's credibility The reason I could theoretically trust Apple though I'm a PC person myself is that Apple has to worry about their customers deserting them if they screw up badly The government doesn't have any such worry it can change the rules by force to get the outcome it This is the ultimate reason why private enterprise is usually more efficient than government